test (汉语水平考试 hànyǔ shuǐpíng kǎoshì), the official way to certify your skills on a basic, intermediate or advanced level. the test involves reading, writing and listening, but no speaking. see the hsk homepage [49] for dates and locations. scholarships[edit] in order to promote its culture and language, the chinese government offers scholarships to foreigners who want to study in china. partial scholarships will cover the tuition fees of the study of your choice. full scholarships cover pretty much everything, including books, rent, some medical coverage, and a monthly allowance for food and expenses. although studying pins you down to a 